  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal framework surrounding money laundering:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Basel Committee Guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n3. Regulatory Requirements\n- Customer Due Diligence (CDD)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) processes\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Monetary fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Imprisonment\n- Corporate liability\n- Individual criminal prosecution\n\n5. Reporting Obligations\n- Financial institutions must report suspicious transactions\n- Mandatory disclosure of large cash transactions\n- Cross-border financial movement reporting\n\n6. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk-based approach\n- Internal controls\n- Regular audits\n- Staff training programs\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing\n- Extradition treaties\n- Joint investigations\n- Mutual legal assistance\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
